  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Technical Superintendent (Tankers)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Oversee day-to-day technical management of assigned vessels, including maintenance, repairs, and dry-dockings.</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with flag state, class, statutory regulations, and company technical standards.</p></li><li><p>Manage planned maintenance systems (PMS), defect reporting, and technical documentation.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with shipyards, service providers, makers, and suppliers for repairs and spares.</p></li><li><p>Prepare and control technical budgets, monitor costs, and ensure cost-effective execution.</p></li><li><p>Provide technical support to vessels, Masters, and Chief Engineers, including troubleshooting and incident follow-ups.</p></li><li><p>Participate in dry-dock planning, execution, and post-dock evaluation.</p></li><li><p>Work closely with HSQE, operations, and commercial teams to ensure safe and efficient vessel operations.</p></li><li><p>Review technical performance data and implement improvement initiatives.</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Class 1 or Class 2 Marine Engineer Certificate, or equivalent maritime engineering qualification.</p></li><li><p>Prior experience as a Technical Superintendent managing tanker vessels is strongly preferred.</p></li><li><p>Strong knowledge of marine engineering systems, dry-docking, and regulatory requirements.</p></li><li><p>Good budgeting, planning, and stakeholder management skills.</p></li><li><p>Proactive, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple vessels simultaneously.</p></li></ul>",
